    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals & Automotive Professional. Background: Stone-50 (Paper), Text: Slate-800, Accents: Burnt Orange (Action) and Slate Blue (Trust). -->
    
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         The app is structured as a "Vertical Narrative Dashboard." 
         1. Sidebar Navigation: Allows non-linear exploration but suggests a logical flow (Vision -> Product -> Market -> Financials -> Future).
         2. Dynamic Content Area: Prevents page reloads, keeping the user immersed.
         3. Interactive Cards & Charts: Users must click or hover to reveal details, simulating the "discovery" process of due diligence. 
         4. Why this structure? Pitch decks are often static. This structure turns the pitch into a functional app, proving the team's digital competence while making dense business data (market analysis, financials) digestible via interaction.
    -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Overview (Mission/Vision): Text Cards + Hover Effects. Goal: Inform. Justification: Needs impact and readability.
         2. Product (Service Flow): Interactive Step-Process (CSS/JS). Goal: Explain. Justification: Shows the "Convenience" value prop visually without SVGs.
         3. Market (Competitors): Radar Chart (Chart.js). Goal: Compare. Justification: Visualizes Drive Drop's strengths (Convenience/Price) vs. Dealerships/Local Mechanics effectively.
         4. Financials (Projections): Line & Bar Combination Chart. Goal: Forecast. Justification: Visualizes the "20% Annual Growth" and "50% Customer Base Increase" targets found in the report.
         5. Future (Milestones): Interactive Timeline. Goal: Roadmap. Justification: Breaks down the 5-year plan (App, Expansion) into digestible milestones.
    -->

    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

